CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Strike Aid - Men of the Hotel and Restaurant Employees Union, Local 237, distribute hot coffee and doughnuts to let striking steel workers know they're with them. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Striking steelworkers receiving coffee from men of the Hotel and Restaurant Employees Union, Local 237, one man holding sign reading "Hold the line, we are with you all the way Local 237 AFL"
